tyle="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">HB</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">Rent-free weeks - technically </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">misleading description as there are no "rent-free" weeks. However, Registered Providers will, as long as the tenant is not in arrears with rent, acc</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">ept payment made over 48 or 50 weeks.  </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">HB</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> awards are subsequently made over 52 weeks with the weekly payment being apportioned accordingly.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">SSSC requires the </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">LA</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> to make </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">an</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> assessment o</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">f</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> the size criteria to apply to a </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">HB</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> claim if the tenant is deemed to have too many bedrooms that their circumstances permit. </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> Further</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> considerations to take into account </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">are</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> the presence of disabled children, the need for an overnight carer, foster children or adult children serving in HM F</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">orces.</span></li></ul><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.88pt; padding-left:3.12pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">The introduction of SSSC has provided an invaluable opportunity for </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">LAs</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> to forge </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">even </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">closer links with Registered Housing Providers</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> initially in the identification of affected cases and the exchange of information but subsequently in the determina</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">tion of </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">DHP </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">awards and ensuring that these awards are reasonable</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> fair and sustainable </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">- </span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">as well as encouraging affected tenants to explor</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt"> alternative housing options. </span></li><li style="font-family:DIN-Regular; font-size:11pt; line-heig